text: Firefighters were called to Wasilla Bible Church in Wasilla, Alaska, about 9:40 p.m. Friday and found flames and smoke coming out windows at the back of the three-story structure, said James Steele, chief of the Central Mat-Su Fire Department.
title: An overnight fire Friday at Alaska Gov. Sarah Palin's home church caused an estimated $ 1 million in damage, and investigators say it could be the work of an arsonist.
